msgid "Local network access to your server"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/05.domains/dns_local_network.mdx:6
msgid ""
"After completing your server installation, it is possible that your domain "
"will not be accessible through the local network. This is an issue known as "
"[hairpinning](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hairpinning) - a feature that is "
"not well supported by some internet routers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/05.domains/dns_local_network.mdx:8
msgid "To solve this issue you can:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/05.domains/dns_local_network.mdx:11
msgid "configure your router's DNS"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/05.domains/dns_local_network.mdx:11
msgid "or alternatively - your /etc/hosts files on your clients workstation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/05.domains/dns_local_network.mdx:12
#, no-wrap
msgid "Find the local IP address of your server"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/05.domains/dns_local_network.mdx:15
msgid "First you need to find out the local IP of your server"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/05.domains/dns_local_network.mdx:19
msgid ""
"either using the tricks listed [here](/admin/get_started/post_install/"
"find_ip)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/05.domains/dns_local_network.mdx:19
msgid ""
"or if in the webadmin, in the Diagnosis section, under Internet "
"Connectivity, IPv4, click on 'Details' and you should find an entry for "
"'Local IP'"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/05.domains/dns_local_network.mdx:19
msgid "or using the command line on the server : `hostname -I`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/05.domains/dns_local_network.mdx:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configure DNS on your Internet router"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/05.domains/dns_local_network.mdx:23
msgid ""
"The goal here is to create a network wide redirection handled by your "
"router. The idea is to create a DNS redirection to your server's IP. You "
"should access your router's configuration and look for DNS configuration, "
"then add a redirection to your server's IP (e.g. redirect `yunohost.local` "
"to `192.168.1.21`)."
msgstr ""

